# clock_ui

UI state-machine that ties together all hardware drivers and manages all
interactive setting modes.  `main.c` only needs to call `clock_ui_tick()`
every loop iteration; the library handles display updates, LED ring output,
and buzzer feedback internally for every setting mode.

## Modes (`ui_mode_t`)

| Mode                  | Description                                    |
| --------------------- | ---------------------------------------------- |
| `UI_MODE_CLOCK`       | Normal operation — shows live time             |
| `UI_MODE_SET_H`       | Edit hours   (blinking left digits on TM1637)  |
| `UI_MODE_SET_M`       | Edit minutes (blinking right digits on TM1637) |
| `UI_MODE_SET_BRIGHT`  | Edit LED ring brightness                       |
| `UI_MODE_SET_QUIET_F` | Edit quiet-time start hour                     |
| `UI_MODE_SET_QUIET_T` | Edit quiet-time end hour                       |

After **10 seconds** of inactivity in any setting mode the UI returns to
`UI_MODE_CLOCK` without saving, and plays `buzzer_beep_cancel()`.

## API

```c
// Set default brightness, quiet-time window.  Call once at startup.
void clock_ui_init(uint8_t brightness, uint8_t quiet_from, uint8_t quiet_to);

// Main update function — call every ~50 ms.
//   hour / minute  current time read from RTC
//   ev             latest button event (BTN_NONE if none)
// Returns the current ui_mode_t (useful for main.c to decide what to render).
ui_mode_t clock_ui_tick(uint8_t hour, uint8_t minute, btn_event_t ev);

// Access current user-configurable settings.
const ui_settings_t *clock_ui_settings(void);
```

## Settings structure (`ui_settings_t`)

```c
typedef struct {
    uint8_t brightness;   // LED ring brightness 1–64
    uint8_t quiet_from;   // Start of silent period (hour, 0–23)
    uint8_t quiet_to;     // End   of silent period (hour, 0–23)
    bool    sound_mute;   // Manual mute override
} ui_settings_t;
```

## Button mapping in `UI_MODE_CLOCK`

| Gesture              | Action                           |
| -------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| Both — hold          | Enter time-set (hours)           |
| Left  — hold         | Toggle sound mute                |
| Right — hold         | Enter brightness setting         |
| Left  — double click | Enter quiet-time start setting   |
| Right — double click | Enter quiet-time end setting     |
| Both  — click        | Show mute status (beep feedback) |

## Button mapping in setting modes

| Gesture           | Action                     |
| ----------------- | -------------------------- |
| Right click       | Increment value (+1)       |
| Left  click       | Decrement value (−1)       |
| Right / Left hold | Fast increment / decrement |
| Both  click       | Next field / back          |
| Both  hold        | Save and return to clock   |
| Timeout (10 s)    | Cancel and return to clock |
